---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/museum.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Museum of Dumb Ideas"
  description="A curated collection of questionable projects, purchased domains, abandoned plans, and ideas that somehow became worthwhile."
>
  <div class="museum-page">
    <header class="museum-hero">
      <p class="museum-kicker">Brad Cooke Presents</p>
      <h1>Museum of Dumb Ideas</h1>

      <p class="museum-subtitle">
        A carefully curated collection of questionable projects, unnecessary
        domain purchases, abandoned plans, and ideas that were funny enough to
        preserve.
      </p>
    </header>

    <aside class="curator-note">
      <h2>Curator's Note</h2>

      <p>
        Not every idea needs a business plan. Some ideas are useful. Some are
        terrible. Occasionally, one survives long enough to become something
        worthwhile.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Museum exists to preserve all three.
      </p>
    </aside>

    <section class="museum-section">
      <p class="museum-kicker">Now Showing</p>
      <h2>Current Exhibits</h2>

      <div class="exhibit-grid">
        <article class="exhibit-card">
          <p class="exhibit-status">On Permanent Display</p>
          <h3>OmeletYouFinish.com</h3>

          <p>
            An ambitious attempt to combine breakfast, travel, and a Kanye West
            joke into a coherent online property.
          </p>

          <p>
            <a href="/museum/omelet-you-finish/">View exhibit →</a>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="exhibit-card">
          <p class="exhibit-status">Under Restoration</p>
          <h3>The Jeep Incident</h3>

          <p>
            An early demonstration that confidence and four-wheel drive are not
            the same thing.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="exhibit-card">
          <p class="exhibit-status">Escaped Collection</p>
          <h3>Bread Pitt</h3>

          <p>
            A sourdough joke that refused to remain a joke and developed a
            filmography-based career of its own.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="museum-section">
      <p class="museum-kicker">Museum Map</p>
      <h2>Future Wings</h2>

      <div class="wing-grid">
        <article class="wing-card">
          <h3>Hall of Purchased Domains</h3>
          <p>
            Evidence that registering the domain often happens well before
            thinking through the rest of the idea.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="wing-card">
          <h3>Half-Baked Projects</h3>
          <p>
            Projects that made it past the idea stage but wisely stopped before
            production.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="wing-card">
          <h3>Questionable Experiments</h3>
          <p>
            Plans that began with confidence and ended with lessons, cleanup,
            or outside assistance.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="wing-card">
          <h3>Unexpected Successes</h3>
          <p>
            Ideas that escaped containment and accidentally became real
            projects.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="museum-footer">
      <p>
        The collection remains incomplete because questionable decisions are
        still being made.
      </p>

      <p><a href="/">Return to BradCooke.com</a></p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>
